        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4310_14908_000002_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4310/14908/4310_14908_000002_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4310",
        "content": "THE GREYHOUND",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-slow_e-normal",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "very slow",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4310_14908_000003_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4310/14908/4310_14908_000003_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4310",
        "content": "The earliest references to him are far back in the primitive ages, long before he was beautifully depicted by Assyrian artists, straining at the leash or racing after his prey across the desert sands.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4310_14908_000003_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4310/14908/4310_14908_000003_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4310",
        "content": "The Egyptians loved him and appreciated him centuries before the pyramids were built.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4310_14908_000003_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4310/14908/4310_14908_000003_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4310",
        "content": "In those days he wore a feathered tail, and his ears were heavy with a silken fringe of hair.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4310_14908_000004_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4310/14908/4310_14908_000004_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4310",
        "content": "That the Greyhound is \"comely in going,\" as well as in repose, was recognised very early by the Greeks, whose artists were fond of introducing this graceful animal as an ornament in their decorative workmanship.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4310_14908_000004_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4310/14908/4310_14908_000004_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4310",
        "content": "Usually these Greek Greyhounds are represented with prick ears, but occasionally the true rose ear is shown.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4310_14908_000005_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4310/14908/4310_14908_000005_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4310",
        "content": "All writings in connection with Greyhounds point to the high estimation in which the dog has always been held.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-slow_e-normal",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "slow",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4310_14908_000006_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4310/14908/4310_14908_000006_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4310",
        "content": "It was not until the reign of Queen Elizabeth that coursing in England was conducted under established rules.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4310_14908_000006_000001",
